MATCH_TOOL: Write
MATCH_PATTERN: \.superpowers/brainstorm/.*/content/.*\.html
ADVISORY: |
  Brainstorm visual companion — known traps:

  1. KEEP HTML SIMPLE. Complex CSS (deep nesting, pseudo-elements, animations,
     absolute positioning) breaks rendering in the companion frame. Prefer flat
     class hierarchies, inline styles for one-offs, minimal CSS. If a mockup
     renders broken, simplify the CSS rather than debugging the frame template.

  2. SERVER ONLY SERVES HTML. No images, fonts, or other assets from subdirectories.
     For local images: use external URLs (CDN, Google Fonts) or base64 data URIs
     (<100KB). Relative src paths like "personas/foo.png" will 404.

  3. SERVER DIES FREQUENTLY (often before the 30-min timeout). Before writing
     content, check that $STATE_DIR/server-info exists. If the server has died:
     restart with start-server.sh, note the NEW port and session directory, copy
     content to the new session's content/ directory. Old session files are orphaned.
     Always tell the user the updated URL after a restart.
